249
00:30:49.291 --> 00:30:51.783
Someone will move
against the Salamancas.

250
00:30:53.462 --> 00:30:55.931
Which brings war.

251
00:30:57.366 --> 00:31:00.359
Which brings chaos.

252
00:31:02.004 --> 00:31:03.495
Which brings...

253
00:31:04.306 --> 00:31:05.797
the D.E.A.

254
00:33:06.829 --> 00:33:08.229
What's up?

255
00:33:08.397 --> 00:33:10.730
It's busted again.

256
00:33:19.341 --> 00:33:21.207
It's just the chain.

257
00:33:21.510 --> 00:33:24.275
Want me to do it or you
wanna try it yourself?

258
00:33:26.815 --> 00:33:28.306
Okay.

259
00:33:29.218 --> 00:33:31.949
This is the last time. so watch.

260
00:33:32.855 --> 00:33:34.448
All right.

261
00:33:34.623 --> 00:33:38.924
So you take this. give it a
little play. right about there.

262
00:33:39.361 --> 00:33:42.160
Loop it around
the big gear. yeah?

263
00:33:42.331 --> 00:33:43.924
And then...

264
00:33:45.601 --> 00:33:47.763
- That's all there is to it.
- Okay.

265
00:33:51.173 --> 00:33:53.768
- And?
- Thanks. Dad.

266
00:33:57.980 --> 00:34:00.609
Make sure Mom
knows where you are.

267
00:34:43.659 --> 00:34:45.525
Hi. Denise.

268
00:34:46.428 --> 00:34:48.397
Uh. yeah. it's Barry.

269
00:34:48.564 --> 00:34:52.501
Uh. listen. could you let Mr. Eglin
know I'm gonna be late this morning?

270
00:34:53.335 --> 00:34:55.668
I might miss the staff meeting.

271
00:34:57.506 --> 00:35:00.999
No. no. Car troubles.
Probably just a dead battery.

272
00:35:01.376 --> 00:35:04.175
Yeah. I know. I know.

273
00:35:04.346 --> 00:35:06.440
Practically brand-new.

274
00:35:06.882 --> 00:35:08.942
Okay. thanks.

275
00:36:11.580 --> 00:36:14.516
Bruce had the speed. He could
kick you before you saw him move.

276
00:36:14.683 --> 00:36:17.949
- You ever watched a Liston fight?
- We're talking about what?

277
00:36:18.120 --> 00:36:21.818
- Boxing? That's something else.
- No. we're talking a street fight.

278
00:36:21.990 --> 00:36:25.722
- Street fight? Great. so Bruce can kick.
- We're not talking a movie fight.

279
00:36:25.894 --> 00:36:29.592
- We're talking about weight. about reach.
- Boxing is a sport.

280
00:36:29.765 --> 00:36:31.666
Martial arts is life and death.

281
00:36:31.833 --> 00:36:33.995
Look. I don't care
how fast you are.

282
00:36:34.169 --> 00:36:37.037
Muhammad Ali hits you.
you're going down. that's a fact.

283
00:36:37.205 --> 00:36:39.231
If he hits you.

284
00:36:39.408 --> 00:36:42.503
Bruce Lee. he knows the anatomy.

285
00:36:42.678 --> 00:36:44.840
He's got the moves. He's
gonna find an opening.

286
00:36:45.013 --> 00:36:47.505
Without power. the
opening doesn't mean squat.

287
00:36:47.683 --> 00:36:50.778
- How much does he weigh? 
- I don't know. Maybe a buck-thirty.

288
00:36:50.952 --> 00:36:55.048
Ali was the heavyweight champ.
He's got 100 pounds on Lee.

289
00:36:55.223 --> 00:36:57.055
Bruce feints for Ali's head.

290
00:36:57.225 --> 00:37:00.889
But he goes low and sweeps him
to the deck. Ali goes down hard.

291
00:37:01.063 --> 00:37:02.361
It's all over.

292
00:37:02.531 --> 00:37:04.295
Does he have a gun?

293
00:37:04.466 --> 00:37:07.868
- I'm sorry?
- Does Bruce Lee have a gun?

294
00:37:08.036 --> 00:37:11.165
If he doesn't. it's Ali in
three minutes or less.

295
00:37:11.673 --> 00:37:14.700
See? That's what I'm
saying. That's what I'm say...

296
00:37:15.110 --> 00:37:17.705
Hey. hold on. Wait. wait.

297
00:37:20.182 --> 00:37:23.152
Did you sign. uh.
Tina's birthday card?

298
00:37:23.318 --> 00:37:25.480
- No.
- Would you mind?

299
00:37:26.588 --> 00:37:28.557
Not at all.

300
00:37:33.729 --> 00:37:36.563
- You're out of line.
- I'm saying...

301
00:37:36.732 --> 00:37:39.930
if Lee tried to sweep
Ali's legs. he'll sidestep.

302
00:37:40.102 --> 00:37:42.594
Ali was fast for his size. yes.

303
00:37:42.771 --> 00:37:45.605
But if he gets hit with a low
kick. he won't know what to do.

304
00:37:45.774 --> 00:37:48.107
I know what he'll
do. He'll do just fine.

305
00:37:48.276 --> 00:37:49.574
You're nuts.

306
00:37:49.745 --> 00:37:51.611
- Thanks.
- Yeah.

307
00:37:51.780 --> 00:37:54.511
Bruce was a brawler.
okay? He gets in quick...

308
00:40:14.322 --> 00:40:15.449
I got it.

309
00:40:15.624 --> 00:40:17.183
Uh. yeah?

310
00:40:18.059 --> 00:40:20.187
Ramirez. team leader.

311
00:40:20.362 --> 00:40:21.489
Yes. sir.

312
00:40:21.663 --> 00:40:23.996
Ramirez. what do
you think you're up to?

313
00:40:24.466 --> 00:40:27.265
We're just pulling an
order. Something wrong?

314
00:40:27.435 --> 00:40:30.564
May I ask why none of your
guys are wearing a lift belt?

315
00:40:31.706 --> 00:40:33.231
Lift belt?

316
00:40:33.408 --> 00:40:35.536
- We don't usually...
- Stop what you're doing.

317
00:40:35.710 --> 00:40:39.340
Go to the equipment room.
You get lift belts and gloves.

318
00:40:39.514 --> 00:40:42.848
You use them. Rules
are rules. got me?

319
00:40:43.018 --> 00:40:44.281
Sure. Sure. Okay.

320
00:40:44.452 --> 00:40:46.284
On the double.

321
00:40:46.454 --> 00:40:49.481
Hey. hold up. Shut it down.

322
00:40:49.658 --> 00:40:51.456
Shut it down.

323
00:41:12.314 --> 00:41:13.805
Uh. excuse me.

324
00:41:13.982 --> 00:41:15.712
I think this belongs to you.

325
00:41:16.885 --> 00:41:19.787
Oh. my God. Ha. ha.

326
00:41:20.188 --> 00:41:22.953
Thank you. Where
did you find it?

327
00:41:23.625 --> 00:41:25.457
I need to talk to your manager.

328
00:41:26.995 --> 00:41:29.931
I waltz through security
with someone else's ID.

329
00:41:30.098 --> 00:41:32.124
Nobody gives me a second look.

330
00:41:32.701 --> 00:41:37.264
When the rightful owner shows up.
there's no facility-wide badge check.

331
00:41:37.439 --> 00:41:40.466
I find access doors left
unlocked or propped open.

332
00:41:40.642 --> 00:41:42.770
Passwords written
on Post-it notes.

333
00:41:42.944 --> 00:41:47.405
Warehouse workers are using pen
and paper instead of electronic devices...

334
00:41:47.582 --> 00:41:49.847
which leaves you
open to pilfering.

335
00:41:50.018 --> 00:41:52.510
You got duplicate
routing numbers on cargo.

336
00:41:52.687 --> 00:41:57.352
Surveillance camera blind spots on
the north and the east side of the floor.

337
00:41:57.525 --> 00:42:01.587
Inventory documents going into
the trash instead of being shredded.

338
00:42:01.763 --> 00:42:06.326
Not to mention loading equipment
driven at unsafe speeds...

339
00:42:06.501 --> 00:42:07.696
- Wait. Wait.
- And crews...

340
00:42:07.869 --> 00:42:11.465
- Wait. hold on. Who are you exactly?
- Disregarding safe...

341
00:42:11.973 --> 00:42:13.601
Ehrmantraut.

342
00:42:13.775 --> 00:42:15.505
Security consultant.

343
00:42:17.145 --> 00:42:20.445
Well. all due respect. I don't know
anything about a security consultant.

344
00:42:20.615 --> 00:42:22.607
Well. you wouldn't. would you?

345
00:42:23.284 --> 00:42:25.810
Maybe you'd best call corporate.

346
00:42:25.987 --> 00:42:29.685
Try Lydia Rodarte-Quayle.

347
00:42:48.410 --> 00:42:50.402
I'm truly sorry. Jimmy.

348
00:42:50.578 --> 00:42:52.638
Thank you. Cliff.
I appreciate that.

349
00:42:55.350 --> 00:42:56.511
Hey.

350
00:42:56.684 --> 00:42:58.312
He was a hell of a lawyer.

351
00:42:58.486 --> 00:42:59.647
Yes. he was.

352
00:43:02.490 --> 00:43:03.981
Jimmy.

353
00:43:04.592 --> 00:43:07.494
We're gonna miss him so much.

354
00:43:07.662 --> 00:43:08.994
Thank you. Brenda.

355
00:43:12.033 --> 00:43:14.730
- I'm sorry for your loss.
- Thanks. Brian.

356
00:43:18.840 --> 00:43:20.570
Jimmy. I'm so sorry.

357
00:43:20.742 --> 00:43:23.302
Oh. thanks. Appreciate that.

358
00:43:48.536 --> 00:43:50.232
<i>Thank you.</i>

359
00:44:28.510 --> 00:44:31.878
I think I owe you the
truth about Chuck.

360
00:44:33.148 --> 00:44:34.912
Those lanterns.

361
00:44:36.451 --> 00:44:40.081
He was living in that house
without electricity for two years.

362
00:44:40.255 --> 00:44:42.724
He knew how to
use those lanterns.

363
00:44:42.891 --> 00:44:47.522
He was careful. I saw it. I know you
did too. There was never a problem.

364
00:44:49.397 --> 00:44:51.798
I know it's a
terrible thing to...

365
00:44:55.036 --> 00:44:57.631
I don't think what
happened was an accident.

366
00:45:07.749 --> 00:45:12.483
You probably heard Chuck
was retiring from HHM.

367
00:45:13.254 --> 00:45:15.314
But that's not the truth.

368
00:45:16.691 --> 00:45:21.152
The truth is that we
had a disagreement...

369
00:45:21.329 --> 00:45:23.264
and I pushed him out.

370
00:45:23.765 --> 00:45:24.789
I made him go.

371
00:45:24.966 --> 00:45:28.403
Chuck was sick for years.
And after the bar hearing...

372
00:45:28.570 --> 00:45:30.937
The bar hearing had
nothing to do with it.

373
00:45:31.739 --> 00:45:33.298
Okay.

374
00:45:33.474 --> 00:45:36.638
The fact is. he started
getting better after that.

375
00:45:37.512 --> 00:45:41.745
He took more of an interest in the firm.
He came to work. We left the lights on.

376
00:45:42.183 --> 00:45:46.883
He was improving until the thing with
the insurance. it wasn't the bar hearing.

377
00:45:48.056 --> 00:45:49.922
The insurance?

378
00:45:50.425 --> 00:45:52.894
It was a ridiculous thing.

379
00:45:55.029 --> 00:45:56.554
I should've just let it go.

380
00:45:56.731 --> 00:45:59.394
I mean. God knows
he's done enough for me.

381
00:45:59.767 --> 00:46:02.862
But he kept pushing and I. um...

382
00:46:03.204 --> 00:46:05.298
I got my back up.

383
00:46:05.907 --> 00:46:07.876
What about the insurance?

384
00:46:08.042 --> 00:46:10.841
It was. uh. our
malpractice insurance.

385
00:46:11.012 --> 00:46:14.141
They found out about Chuck's
condition. raised our rates.

386
00:46:14.749 --> 00:46:18.208
Chuck went ballistic.
He wanted to go to war.

387
00:46:18.386 --> 00:46:20.116
I drew a line.

388
00:46:20.288 --> 00:46:22.280
He wouldn't back down.

389
00:46:22.457 --> 00:46:23.618
So I forced him out.

390
00:46:29.564 --> 00:46:32.432
It never occurred to
me that I could hurt him.

391
00:46:33.368 --> 00:46:35.837
He always seemed so strong.

392
00:46:36.404 --> 00:46:38.134
But he wasn't.

393
00:46:39.607 --> 00:46:42.543
I think he did what
he did because of me.

394
00:46:50.251 --> 00:46:53.244
Well. Howard. I guess
that's your cross to bear.

395
00:47:12.774 --> 00:47:14.640
Look at her go.

396
00:47:16.244 --> 00:47:19.737
So I'm gonna make
coffee. Anybody want some?
